channel.title: Finding my Default Gateway to my Router
channel.description:
Well, if i go into Cmd, and type in "ipconfig", this is what it says [code]Microsoft Windows XP [Version 5.1.2600] (C) Copyright 1985-2001 Microsoft Corp.
C:\Documents and Settings\user>ipconfig 'ipconfig' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.
C:\Documents and Settings\user>[/code] If i do it on my other computer, it works and gives me the default gateway, but if I try to go into my router using that on this computer, it doesn't work. Any idea why?
